  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Tip: This is just to warm your naans later (alternatively, just pop them in the toaster)</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>king prawns</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until cooked through, then transfer them to a plate and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1629302453118-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1629302453118-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1629302453118-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1629302453118-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1629302453118-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> ginger & garlic paste</strong>,<strong> cumin seeds</strong>,<strong> </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>harissa paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>Mediterranean veg mix</strong>,<strong> </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and cook, covered, for 4 min or until starting to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1629302457886-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1629302457886-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1629302457886-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1629302457886-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1629302457886-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>plain naans</strong> to a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 3 min or until the bread is hot (or add to your toaster!)</p><p>In a small bowl, combine the <strong>Greek-style yoghurt </strong>and the <strong>remaining harissa paste </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>harissa yoghurt</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>baby leaf salad</strong>, then pat it dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1629302463455-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1629302463455-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1629302463455-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1629302463455-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1629302463455-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Roll the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p><p>Once the veg has started to soften, return the<strong> cooked prawns </strong>to the pan</p><p>Add the juice<strong> </strong>of the lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]<strong> </span></strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and give everything a good mix up – these are your <strong>harissa & ginger prawns</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>warmed naan </strong>into strips</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1629302477947-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1629302477947-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1629302477947-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1629302477947-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1629302477947-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Spread the <strong>harissa yoghurt</strong> on the plate and top with the <strong>harissa & ginger prawns</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>naan strips</strong> and<strong> salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish everything with the <strong>ground sumac</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 5,
